LOCK TABLES `how_to_applies` WRITE;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `how_to_applies` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `how_to_applies` VALUES (1,'After you’ve found the Apprenticeship you want, apply as\r\nsoon as you can. Places may not be available for long so get down to filling in\r\nall the necessary forms and be sure to confirm meetings with employers. You’re not automatically guaranteed an Apprenticeship place.\r\nThe selection process is like any other job application and you’ll have to show\r\nthat you’re the right person for the job. You may have to go through one or more interviews, and maybe even take some tests.<br><br><b>Who’s eligible?</b><br>You can join an Apprenticeship scheme as long as you are\r\nover the age of 16, living in England, not currently in full-time education and\r\nyou do not have a university degree. Employers will value your enthusiasm and\r\ndesire to learn, as well as your academic achievements, so practical skills and\r\ninterest in your chosen area are very important.<br><b></b><br><b>Contact an employer</b><br>If you’ve found an Apprenticeship within a company that\r\ninterests you then you can approach the employer directly. Before you contact\r\nthem, it’s a good idea to check the company’s website as answers to the most\r\ncommon questions might be there. Remember: you’ll be contacting the company as\r\na potential employee so act professionally – first impressions are important.<br><b><br>Already working?</b><br>If you’ve got a job, why not ask your employer if they’d\r\nconsider taking you on as an apprentice? Point them to the employers’ section\r\nof the National Apprenticeship Service website for more information.<br><br><b>Access to Apprenticeships</b><br>Aged between 16 and 24 but not eligible to take on a full\r\nApprenticeship? Talk to your careers advisor to find out if you are eligibleto join the Access to Apprenticeships\r\nprogramme.<br><b><br>National Apprenticeship Service</b><br>Search for, view and apply for Apprenticeship vacancies\r\nthrough the NAS website, register your details to find out more information, or\r\nuse the NAS helpline for support and general advice.<br><br><b>Equality and diversity</b><br>Apprenticeship programmes are inclusive and must comply with\r\nthe principles of equality and diversity. Employers and learning providers must\r\nnot discriminate against anyone because of age, gender, disability, marital\r\nstatus, sexual orientation, race, religion or belief. Apprenticeships are seen\r\nas a vital route to encourage a more diverse range of individuals to enter\r\ndifferent industries and therefore entry conditions tend to be extremely\r\nflexible.\r\n','2012-11-05 05:06:06','2012-11-12 11:42:39');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `how_to_applies` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

